                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="102485" author="yong.fan" created="Sat, 3 Jan 2015 02:12:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is the side-effect of test_18f failure because of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5301&quot; title=&quot;Test failure sanity-lfsck test_17: (3) unexpected status&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5301&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5301&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="102484" author="yong.fan" created="Sat, 3 Jan 2015 02:11:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Because of injection failure stub in test_18f and such test failed, the layout LFSCK on OST0 did not completed unexpectedly, as to when moved to test_20, the layout LFSCK on OST0 auto resumed before the command to trigger it. Under such case, the MDS0 got -EBUSY when sent LFSCK RPC to the OST0 for trying to trigger layout LFSCK, so the MDS0 thought that there were something wrong on the OST0, so it marked the layout LFSCK status as &quot;partial&quot; on the MDT0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="102374" author="jlevi" created="Mon, 29 Dec 2014 18:20:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nasf,&lt;br/&gt;
Can you please look into this one?&lt;br/&gt;
Thank you!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
